<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Clarification for Covetous Crew et All</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Fernwig Teveril">Fernwig Teveril</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:39 p.m. 19/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Clarification for Covetous Crew et All<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1594" TARGET=_self>Clarification for Covetous Crew et All</A> (The RealmWeaver)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> After being approached in the game by several CC members who

<BR>&gt; misconstrued my earlier comments, I thought I would post a
<BR>&gt; clarification here. I am not "blaming" the travesty of
<BR>&gt; Rallos Zek's lack of roleplaying on Covetous Crew, nor am I
<BR>&gt; singling them out as the source of all bad roleplaying.
<P>hmmm.. what do we have here?
<BR>Elwin,
<P>I would love to tell you that the PVP server is rich in roleplaying. I have even formed a Guild in an attempt to bolster its promise and
<BR>influence, but unfortunately it's pretty much all for not. Entire Guilds have been built around the notion that PVP simply can't mix
<BR>with Roleplaying. (Darkbane Company and Covetous Crew come to mind). I actually have a screenshot of someone saying "This is
<BR>PVP, not roleplaying. PVP and roleplaying have never got along." I translated this as "I'm too power-hungry to actually play the
<BR>game, instead I speed through the levels, then send myself on a power trip by killing people lower than me." CC Rules! Oh, well. I
<BR>respect CC for their knowledge of the game, but they, and those like them, will forever banish roleplaying from PVP server, because
<BR>when the best players don't set an example, all the newbies follow suit. Sorry Elwin, I don't think you will find Roleplaying on Rallos
<BR>Zek, thank CC.
<P>[The RealmWeaver]
<P>-I am not "blaming" the travesty of Rallos Zek's lack of roleplaying on Covetous Crew, nor am I singling them out as the source of all bad roleplaying.
<BR>uhh huh
<BR>-I don't think you will find Roleplaying on Rallos Zek, thank CC.
<BR>uhh huh... two very contradicting posts... which opinion is it?
<P>-Fernwig Teveril
<BR>www.covetouscrew.org
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
